  "instructions": [
    "Soak dried navy beans overnight or pressure-cook with 2 cups water for 30 minutes.",
    "Sauté onion and garlic in a pot over medium heat until soft.",
    "Add tomato paste and mild chili (if using), cook for 1 minute.",
    "Pour in soaked beans and 2 cups water, bring to a boil.",
    "Cover and pressure-cook for 15 minutes until beans are tender.",
    "Stir in spinach, cucumber, and coconut milk, then season with salt.",
    "Simmer for 5 minutes until flavors meld.",
    "Serve hot with a side of rice."
